| 1848 || January || Beginning of migration || Gold is discovered in California, leading to a [[wikipedia:California Gold Rush|California Gold Rush]]. A number of people from China arrive in the United States to participate in the Gold Rush. Before 1848, the total number of Chinese in the United States is only 325; soon, annual immigration from China exceeds this amount.
